headline: Elevance Health Resets 2026 Outlook As Investors Weigh Long Term Payoff
summary: Elevance Health (NYSE:ELV) has issued 2026 guidance calling for a low single digit decline in operating revenue. The company also forecasts lower than previously expected profits for 2026. Management cited sector wide medical cost pressures, changes in Medicaid enrollment, and government program membership declines as key headwinds. Elevance plans to continue investing in its business while targeting profit improvement over the longer term. For you as an investor, this update from Elevance...

headline: ELV Q4 Deep Dive: Margin Pressures and Membership Shifts Shape 2026 Outlook
summary: Health insurance provider Elevance Health (NYSE:EVH) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 9.6% year on year to $49.31 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.33 per share was 7.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
